  IDEATION DOCUMENT  


BRAINSTORMING PROCESS  

Based on the empathy maps and personas created, the following core user needs were identified:
- Employees need quick, private stress relief during work hours
- Relaxation must be personalized to individual stress levels
- Sessions must be short enough to fit into a busy workday
- The experience must feel calming and non-intrusive

 IDEAS GENERATED  

Stress Input Methods:
- Mood check-in via emoji slider on home screen
- Manual survey at start of each session
- Voice tone detection
- Wearable device integration via smartwatch heart rate

Relaxation Features:
- AI-curated music playlists based on stress level
- Mood-based lighting that changes color and brightness
- Aroma diffuser intensity control
- Guided breathing exercises with animated timer
- Short meditation audio sessions

Scheduling and Planning:
- Calendar-based pod booking system
- AI-suggested best time to book based on stress patterns
- Slot availability indicator
- Reschedule and cancel options

Tracking and Progress:
- 7-day stress level graph on home screen
- Before and after stress rating in journal
- Wellness streak tracker
- Progress badges and achievements

Personalization:
- User preference settings for music, aroma, and lighting
- Quick preset modes — Relax, Focus, Sleep, Energy Boost
- MoodSync AI auto-configures pod based on current stress data

 
 5 COMPULSORY FEATURES SELECTED  

1. MoodSync AI — addresses the need for instant personalized relaxation without manual setup
2. Breathe With Me — provides immediate relief through guided breathing at any stress level
3. Pod Scheduler — solves the problem of pod crowding and helps employees plan ahead
4. Post-Session Journal — helps users track improvement and reflect on their mental state over time
5. Stress Tracking Dashboard — gives users visibility of their stress patterns and motivates continued use

 ADDITIONAL FEATURES INCLUDED  

- Wellness streak badge to encourage daily use
- Quick check-in prompt on home screen
- Last session summary card
- Notification bell for session reminders
- AI-recommended booking time based on peak stress hours
- Slot availability indicator on sessions screen
- Quick preset modes: Relax, Focus, Sleep, Energy Boost

IDEAS NOT INCLUDED AND WHY  

- Voice tone stress detection — too complex for a prototype stage
- Wearable device integration — requires hardware and is beyond the scope of an app prototype
- Group meditation sessions — conflicts with the privacy requirement identified in user research
- Gamified leaderboard — could increase competition and stress rather than reduce it
